sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor user as Registry user
  participant browser as Browser
  participant alb as Internal ALB
  participant entra as Microsoft Entra ID
  participant api as Registry API
  participant keyService as Regional ALB public-key endpoint
  participant graphApi as Microsoft Graph
  participant cache as Membership cache
  participant postgres as PostgreSQL

  user->>browser: Open Registry route
  browser->>alb: HTTPS request without ALB session
  alb->>entra: Redirect to tenant authorization endpoint
  entra->>user: Enforce tenant policy, MFA, and consent
  user->>entra: Complete authentication
  entra-->>alb: Authorization response
  alb->>entra: Exchange code and request user information
  entra-->>alb: ID, access, and user-info claims
  alb-->>browser: Set encrypted ALB session cookie and redirect
  browser->>alb: Retry Registry request
  alb->>api: Forward identity, signed OIDC data, and delegated access token

  api->>keyService: Resolve key identifier with bounded timeout and rotation cache
  keyService-->>api: ES256 public key
  api->>api: Verify algorithm, signature, exact signer ARN, issuer, client ID, expiry, and subject match

  alt assertion is invalid
    api-->>browser: Reject request without creating a principal
  else assertion is valid
    api->>cache: Look up subject and configured-group-set membership
    alt current membership result exists
      cache-->>api: Return cached memberships within 60 seconds
    else membership is absent or expired
      loop groups are batched at no more than 20 IDs
        api->>graphApi: POST /me/checkMemberGroups with delegated User.Read token
        graphApi-->>api: Matching configured group IDs
      end
      api->>cache: Coalesce concurrent lookups and cache successful result only
    end
    api->>api: Derive RegistryPrincipal, admin role, and entitled APM IDs
    api->>postgres: Execute query with mandatory AccessContext predicate
    alt requested package is visible
      postgres-->>api: Authorized catalog rows only
      api-->>browser: Session-safe identity and authorized response
    else package is missing or not entitled
      postgres-->>api: No row
      api-->>browser: Return indistinguishable 404 or an authenticated empty catalog
    end
  end

  opt Graph, identity provider, or token validation fails
    api->>api: Fail closed, do not cache the failure, and emit safe telemetry
    api-->>browser: Identity-provider unavailable or unauthorized state
  end
